      <p>During the 2017 long session of the General Assembly, lawmakers passed a budget that revamped the principal pay schedule. The new schedule includes funding for salary increases for most of the state’s principals and changes how principals are paid.
      <p>Previously, principals were paid by the state based on years of experience and number of teachers supervised.</p>
      <p>Under the new schedule, principals are paid based on student population and whether the school did not meet, met, or exceeded academic growth.</p>
      <p>The change caused confusion among administrators. BEST NC, in partnership with EducationNC, created the principal pay calculator below for principals to calculate their salaries under the new pay schedule. </p>
      <p style="font-style:italic;">This calculator is for demonstration purposes. Any questions should be brought to your district’s HR team.</p>
    </div>
